        "created_at": "2025-07-04T03:17:12.846Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>tldr: I‚Äôd love a feature that allows you put the screen security feature to sleep for a short while (e.g., 5 minutes).</p>\n<p>Thanks for the screen security feature!  I like having it on, but I also screenshot signal conversations pretty often.  I realize you can turn it off in settings, so right now, I do, but it‚Äôs a lot of clicking to get to that option twice for a screenshot‚Äîenough that it‚Äôs often not worth it.</p>\n<p>Would you consider adding a ‚Äúsleep‚Äù feature (either in the config options or, ideally, someplace quick like in the dots menu)?  It would just turn of the protection, but turn it back on after some period‚Äîa minute, 5 minutes, etc.  You could even have a config option with the sleep feature off by default to maintain comparable security for people who don‚Äôt want it or don‚Äôt notice.</p>\n<p>Thanks for considering!</p>",
