        "created_at": "2025-07-04T10:13:19.106Z",
        "cooked": "<p>this sounds to me like an OS feature, not a Signal feature.<br>\nalternatively, you‚Äôre looking at something like this existing feature request:</p><aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"1383\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/ba8739/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/lock-the-desktop-app-with-a-password/1383\">Lock the desktop app with a password</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/desktop-feature-requests/20\"><span data-category-id=\"20\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #2D8B39; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF; --parent-category-badge-color: #83B72A;\" data-parent-category-id=\"17\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --has-parent\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Desktop Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    I was excited for the new standalone app, and assumed we would see some much-needed improvements, specifically protecting the app with a password just like the Android app. \nI saw moxie‚Äôs response on github: \n‚ÄúWe‚Äôre not going to be adding any local access control or protection. You can use Chrome profiles, full disk encryption, and a screenlock.‚Äù \n\nThis repsonse is from 2015 - it‚Äôs now 2 months away from 2018 and Wickr is way ahead on the desktop app front, because they have these basic security‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
