        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/chiucs123/{size}/49854_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-04T10:42:51.752Z",
        "cooked": "<p>As far as windows concerned, I believe content protection is enforced whenever a window is created rather than by state, DRM_Flag is considered legacy feature which should not be focused on.</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-my/windows/win32/wmformat/drm-flags\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-my/windows/win32/wmformat/drm-flags\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">learn.microsoft.com</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/362;\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/d/f/df50ff207e6a6ce3b4d58cdf0195308a0fb1e170_2_690x362.png\" class=\"thumbnail\" data-dominant-color=\"D1DDE2\" width=\"690\" height=\"362\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-my/windows/win32/wmformat/drm-flags\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">DRM_Flags - Win32 apps</a></h3>\n\n  <p>The DRM\\_Flags property is used with DRM version 1 content only to specify the rights that will be contained in the local license.</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>However there are reasons to allow an auto-lock feature like the Telegram passcode thing, but the enforcement might not necessarily be DRM related or OS dependent, it can be as simple as having an overlay over everything inside the signal window and put a passcode interface on it.</p>",
